<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
  <TR>
    <TD>
    <FONT FACE="verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif" SIZE=2> Sure, at home, I use (and love) gnome-terminal because of its tabs and anti-aliased fonts.  But at work and at school, I'm restricted to a ghetto ssh terminal connected to my home machine.  And that's where screen really shines.

<p>Screen is great for goofing off at work - in the first window, you've got inscrutable C code, and in the next, you're firing off resumes like mad. <BR>--<br>
<sub> We are a monoculture of horsecock. <a href="http://www.kuro5hin.org/comments/2008/9/20/14025/0248/58#58">Liar</a></sub><BR> </FONT>
    </TD>
